It seems like you're trying to check whether an array is sorted or not in C++. However, there is a logical issue in your is_sorted function. You're accessing arr[i+1] without ensuring that i+1 is a valid index, which can lead to undefined behavior.

To fix this issue, you need to iterate till n-1 in the is_sorted function since you are comparing arr[i] with arr[i+1]
    {
        if(arr[i]>arr[i+1])       
        {
            return false;
        }
    }
    return true;
}

